<subSubSection id="60631E84F0BC36F082296752C21F535C" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="737044DC4229FDB3BD765E59DC272AA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="1991378B4E0DB5656926785EC5CC0BDC" LSID="2379585E-A4DD-530F-A547-2CA1F22AE429" authority="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityName="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityYear="2022" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Dendrocorticiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticiopsis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Dendrocorticiopsis Sheng H. Wu, C.L. Wei &amp; S.H. He</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8A1225D3B492B30C9F9B6C667F9E7AA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5B8C56536E000BBDCC7A4F26F5928F0E" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B58D3B3F106C6528F19692F6DB7908D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41563906436991AB1441E6135D9845CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="7711DB6075048F85A86BB8F70A28B98F" authorityName="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityYear="2022" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Dendrocorticiopsis" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticiopsis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B997ADB17765655C74AA62900179F924" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Dendrocorticiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other genera by having strictly resupinate basidiomata, ivory hymenphore, a compact texture, a monomitic hyphal system, nodose-septate hyphae, encrusted cystidia, dendrohyphidia and ellipsoid to ovoid basidiospores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7996D7593273C451B05ECC752035D778" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="D2C4A2103F5E0E40F4529260733CFF99" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4776CE07150C749858835D854D5216B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Basidiomata resupinate, effused, adnate, membranaceous. Hymenial surface brownish ivory, grayish ivory to lilac ivory, smooth. Hyphal system monomitic; generative hyphae nodose-septate, colorless, slightly thick- to thick-walled. Subiculum uniform, with compact texture, usually with crystal masses; hyphae fairly horizontal. Hymenial layer thickening, with compact texture, usually with oily materials, hyphae more or less vertical. Dendrohyphidia numerous, thick-walled toward base, colorless. Cystidia clavate, apically with resinous materials. Basidia clavate to subclavate, 4-sterigmata, thick-walled toward base. Basidiospores ellipsoid to ovoid, sometimes broadly ellipsoid, smooth, thin-walled or occasionally slightly thick-walled, negative in 
<normalizedToken id="0E27F6A629329CD261F3DD261BE776C4" originalValue="Melzer’s">Melzer's</normalizedToken>
reagent, acyanophilous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6F4E5BDFA606CC2940B3E97DD6724DA8" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="type species">
<paragraph id="A2D9AF0FB91C6610840BBED68B310ABC" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A2B73A7CAED662C589B786D42EB8254" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="DF913196E528F2D0314D1260D8B6D2F8" authorityName="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityYear="2022" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Dendrocorticiopsis" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="C1EA0D2379EB59E8C28B8F70FD143A80" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="388A987FBC805339D9493923280E5F01" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B84511E1D1CCD8B66ADD84A2C6CD6429" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="448F3CFE955892308ACE4F94CFCA4B4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="341B610A73F841A017DE3E24C96582E6" authorityName="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityYear="2022" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Dendrocorticiopsis" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticiopsis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4AD1FB8B724B3FA8C67D62329596518E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Dendrocorticiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the morphological resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="14840A5171D8ECA29EC38BEFC50F0087" authorityName="M.J.Larsen &amp; R.L.Gilbertson" authorityYear="1974" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Corticiaceae" genus="Dendrocorticium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticium" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="043C7761EEDB6D1F063BDF922BED99DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Dendrocorticium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
